    "body": "## Purpose\r\n\r\nFix the ROCm Qwen3.5 accuracy regression apparently introduced by #40711 by skipping the optional AITER Triton GDN decode fast-path for non-interleaved GDN projection layouts.\r\n\r\nThe fused AITER decode path added in #40711 is intended for the Qwen3-Next interleaved GQA layout. Qwen3.5 uses a non-interleaved `[q, k, v, z]` and `[b, a]` projection layout, so sending those packed tensors directly to the fused reshape kernel can read the wrong columns. This change keeps the AITER fast-path enabled for interleaved layouts, while routing non-interleaved layouts through the existing generic GDN core path that performs the correct split and rearrange.\r\n\r\nAI assistance was used for this PR.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- Run Qwen3.5 GSM8K `lm_eval` before and after the patch with the same ROCm runtime image and server settings.\r\n- Run changed-files pre-commit checks.\r\n\r\n## Test Result\r\n\r\nQwen3.5 GSM8K `lm_eval`, `limit=100`, `ROCM_AITER_FA`, `VLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER=1`, `VLLM_ROCM_SHUFFLE_KV_CACHE_LAYOUT=0`, runtime image `vllm/vllm-openai-rocm:nightly-bf610c2f56764e1b30bc6065f4ceace3d6e59036`:\r\n\r\n| Run | flexible-extract | strict-match |\r\n|---|---:|---:|\r\n| Before patch | 0.01 ± 0.01 | 0.00 ± 0.00 |\r\n| With this patch | 0.92 ± 0.0273 | 0.91 ± 0.0288 |\r\n\r\nEquivalent `lm_eval` command used against the running local vLLM server:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nlm_eval \\\r\n  --model local-completions \\\r\n  --model_args model=Qwen/Qwen3.5-397B-A17B-FP8,base_url=http://localhost:8000/v1/completions \\\r\n  --tasks gsm8k \\\r\n  --limit 100 \\\r\n  --batch_size 4 \\\r\n  --seed 4321\r\n```\r\n\r\nChanged-files pre-commit checks passed.\r\n\r\nQwen3-Next non-regression rationale: the only new fast-path condition is `self.gqa_interleaved_layout`. Qwen3-Next constructs `GatedDeltaNetAttention` with `gqa_interleaved_layout=True`, so pure decode batches still enter the same AITER fused decode path as before. Qwen3.5 constructs the layer with `gqa_interleaved_layout=False`, which is the newly guarded non-interleaved layout.",
